title: Sidewall, "Regency", 1940–45
creditline: Gift of A.L. Diament and Co.
description: A classical urn containing a large floral bouquet is enclosed in an oval medallion with a frame of delicate molding and leaf motifs. Between large medallions is a small one enclosed with an intricate intercrossing of delicate acanthus scrolls. Reproduced from a French wallpaper printed by Zuber in the early 19th century. Printed in grays and ivory on beige field.
